1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. Bd3 c5 6. O-O Be7 7. Nc3 d5 8. b3 O-O 9. Bb2 Nc6 { The only difference is in the placement of the bishops } { [%csl Ge7,Gd3] } 10. Re1 Rc8 11. Rc1 cxd4 12. exd4 Re8 (12... dxc4 13. bxc4 { [%csl Gc4,Gd4][%cal Gd4d5] }) 13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. Nxd5 Qxd5 15. Be4 Qd7 { The point of the exchange sacrifice is to get the knight to e5 with tempo and then activate our remaining pieces in a kingside attack. The rook on c1 doesn't participate in any mating attack anyway. } { [%cal Gf3e5] } (15... Qd6 { There's still hope in this position. No immediate tactics work, but d5 is coming fast }) 16. Rxc6 Bxc6 17. Ne5 Qb7 18. Bxh7+ Kf8 (18... Kxh7 19. Qh5+ Kg8 20. Qxf7+ Kh7 21. Re3 { [%cal Ge3h3] } 21... Bxg2 22. d5!! { Deflecting the queen from defending the 7th rank! } { [%cal Gg2d5] } (22. Qg6+ Kg8 { [%cal Gd4d5,Gb7d5] } 23. Rg3 { [%cal Gg6g7] } 23... Bf6 24. Rxg2) (22. Rg3 Bf6 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gb7f7] } 23. Qg6+ (23. Rxg7+ Bxg7 24. d5 (24. Qxb7 Bxb7) 24... Qxf7) 23... Kg8 24. Qxf6) 22... Qxd5 { [%cal Gb7g7] } 23. Qg6+ Kg8 24. Rg3 (24. Nd7 { [%cal Gb2g7,Gg6g7] }) 24... Bf6 { [%cal Gg6f6] } 25. Qxf6) 19. Qh5 Bb4 { [%cal Gb7f7] } 20. Bd3 { [%cal Gb4a3] } 20... g6 (20... Bxe1 21. Ba3+ (21. Ng6+ fxg6 (21... Kg8 22. Qh8#) 22. Ba3+ Re7 (22... Qe7! { [%cal Gd3g6,Ge7a3,Gh5h8,Gf8e7] } 23. Bxe7+ Kxe7 24. Qxg6 { White doesn't have enough material! }) 23. Bxg6 { [%cal Gh5h8] } 23... Kg8 24. Qh7+ Kf8 25. Qh8#) (21. Qh8+ Ke7 22. Ba3+ (22. Qxg7) 22... Kd8) 21... Re7 (21... Kg8 22. Qh7#) 22. Qxf7#) 21. Qh6+ Ke7 { [%cal Gb4e1] } 22. d5 Bxe1 (22... Bxd5 23. Qh4+ Kf8 (23... Kd6 24. Qf4 { [%cal Gf4d6] }) 24. Nd7+ { [%cal Gb2f6] } 24... Qxd7 (24... Kg8 25. Qh8#) 25. Bf6 { [%cal Gh4h8] }) 23. Ba3+ Kd8 24. Qh4+ Kc7 25. dxc6 { [%cal Gb7c6] } 25... Qa8 26. Qf6 { [%cal Gf6f7,Gf7d7] } 26... b5 27. Bc5 { [%csl Gc8,Ge8,Ga8] } 27... Rcd8 28. Qxf7+ Kc8 29. Bxb5 { [%cal Gb5a6] } 29... a6 30. Qd7+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } 30... Rxd7 31. cxd7+ { [%cal Gd7e8] } 31... Kc7 32. dxe8=Q